WEBVTT

00:55.630 --> 00:56.676
Shit.

01:04.690 --> 01:06.681
It's, uh...
it’s
5/7ybum mar/'anum.

01:07.650 --> 01:09.140
Milk thistle.
It's good for the liver.

01:11.860 --> 01:16.399
Why is it that a man who is
so obsessed with his own longevity...

01:17.320 --> 01:20.904
can be so careless with the people
who control his fate?

01:22.410 --> 01:26.323
The Hand is concerned with
this rebellious streak you've shown.

01:27.250 --> 01:29.411
You left the confines
of your penthouse.

01:29.590 --> 01:32.297
I explained that already.
There was someone claiming to be...

01:32.460 --> 01:33.700
Danny Rand.

01:34.800 --> 01:36.870
The lost heir to your company, yes.

01:38.180 --> 01:40.501
He and Madame Gao
met earlier tonight.

01:41.810 --> 01:44.381
She finds it odd
that you failed to mention

01:44.560 --> 01:50.146
the man whose identity you helped restore
is also the legendary Iron Fist,

01:50.900 --> 01:52.606
the sworn enemy of the Hand.

01:52.860 --> 01:54.646
Danny Rand doesn't
even know I'm alive.

01:55.570 --> 01:58.061
I have no idea
what an Iron Fist is.

01:58.360 --> 01:59.611
Sounds like a sex toy.

02:02.870 --> 02:05.577
Maybe you really are
telling us the truth right now

02:05.750 --> 02:09.379
and you really have no idea
what you brought into this company.

02:10.630 --> 02:12.871
Maybe you really
are just a fool.

02:14.300 --> 02:16.916
And Madame Gao
can forgive foolishness...

02:22.300 --> 02:25.019
...but not without punishment.

02:27.640 --> 02:29.096
Vando...

02:30.230 --> 02:31.800
he was a fool once, too.

02:32.230 --> 02:33.470
Twice, actually.

02:34.530 --> 02:37.067
But he has a constant reminder
of his failure.

02:38.150 --> 02:40.903
The fingers were
because he screwed up.

02:42.160 --> 02:44.572
The tongue was
because he lied about it.

02:44.580 --> 02:45.649
The real question is,

02:46.450 --> 02:48.452
how big
a reminder do you need?

02:48.660 --> 02:50.742
Hey, listen to me.
I've done nothing wrong.

02:51.080 --> 02:54.993
I swear on the lives of my children,
I have nothing to do with Danny Rand.

02:57.210 --> 02:58.962
Harold, we have a problem.

03:51.890 --> 03:52.936
You killed them.

03:53.190 --> 03:56.478
What-- What choice did I have?
They were going to kill you, Danny.

03:59.570 --> 04:01.106
Why didn't you
summon the Iron Fist?

04:02.780 --> 04:04.020
I can't.

04:06.160 --> 04:08.071
I just used it
at the tournament.

04:10.200 --> 04:11.280
It drains my chi.

04:11.710 --> 04:14.577
Oh. The tournament?
That's where you met her?

04:15.250 --> 04:16.740
The woman behind the curtain?

04:17.590 --> 04:19.296
She... She challenged me.

04:19.760 --> 04:22.581
IfI won, she said the Hand
would leave New York.

04:23.090 --> 04:24.466
Oh.

04:24.680 --> 04:26.295
But then she
changed the rules.

04:26.890 --> 04:28.130
Well, you know what?
It doesn't matter.

04:28.560 --> 04:31.472
All that matters is they're onto us.
We need to move fast.

04:32.020 --> 04:35.262
- Who is she?
- Ah. Her name is Madame Gao.

04:35.650 --> 04:38.016
I, uh, met her on my deathbed.

04:38.400 --> 04:40.277
She's the one who
made the deal, Danny.

04:40.730 --> 04:43.278
Live in service to the Hand,
or die in the dark.

04:43.950 --> 04:45.235
She said she knew my father.

04:45.570 --> 04:46.559
What?

04:47.070 --> 04:48.571
She said he had no honour.

04:49.370 --> 04:50.735
Wendell never told me.

04:51.620 --> 04:54.248
- Told you what?
- I don't know.

04:56.750 --> 05:00.459
If Wendell knew Gao or the Hand,
he never shared it with me.

05:00.670 --> 05:02.410
I need to find out
how she knew my father.

05:02.590 --> 05:04.330
Hey, don't play her game.

05:04.630 --> 05:05.870
That's what she wants.

05:06.220 --> 05:07.756
Time isn't on our side.

05:08.220 --> 05:10.506
Look how out of control
this has already gotten.

05:11.390 --> 05:13.051
What I had to do to protect you.

05:15.270 --> 05:17.511
I don't know how much more of this
I can take.

05:19.150 --> 05:22.859
You know
what needs to be done to end this, Danny.

05:24.530 --> 05:25.815
What do we do with the bodies?

05:28.910 --> 05:31.947
I'll, uh... I'll take care of 'em.
I'll make 'em disappear.

05:32.410 --> 05:33.536
Gao will know they're missing,

05:33.700 --> 05:37.739
but as long as it looks as though
they did their job before they left...

05:40.920 --> 05:41.989
What job?

05:43.760 --> 05:45.625
To remind me of my mistakes.

07:04.250 --> 07:06.582
Do you understand
how stupid that was?

07:08.720 --> 07:10.210
What if someone had
seen you In there?

07:11.510 --> 07:14.252
I don't think anyone would recognise us
from the country club, Joy.

07:16.180 --> 07:17.920
Oh, come on.

07:27.990 --> 07:31.062
- You're slipping.
- I'm fine.

07:31.360 --> 07:32.406
You're fine?

07:33.450 --> 07:34.986
You're fine, like when I came
in the other night

07:35.080 --> 07:36.866
and I found you passed out
on your couch?

07:37.580 --> 07:39.616
I told you,
I took a muscle relaxer.

07:40.040 --> 07:41.450
What else have you been taking?

07:41.620 --> 07:43.247
I don't need your bullshit, Joy.

07:43.790 --> 07:46.702
You have no idea what my life is like.
No goddamn idea.

07:46.880 --> 07:49.508
- Because you won't tell me!
- I can't!

07:50.510 --> 07:52.171
I...

07:55.850 --> 07:57.806
You need help, Ward.

08:00.810 --> 08:04.348
What I need is for you
to stay out of my business.

08:04.940 --> 08:07.226
I have everything under control.

08:08.190 --> 08:11.023
Yeah. Yeah, well,
you know, I can see that.

08:16.580 --> 08:17.729
Who's Frank Stein?

08:19.870 --> 08:22.031
- Is he your dealer?
- No.

08:22.920 --> 08:25.161
Then who is he?

08:25.830 --> 08:26.956
Tell me.

08:33.260 --> 08:34.249
Fine.

08:34.970 --> 08:36.085
Enjoy your secrets.

08:48.020 --> 08:49.226
It's late.

08:49.530 --> 08:51.350
Wasn ’1' sure you
were gonna pick up this time.

08:52.070 --> 08:54.197
- I’m glad you did.
- What do you want?

08:54.910 --> 08:58.732
I need your help with something
over at the penthouse. It's important.

08:59.160 --> 09:00.730
Real/y not a good time.

09:01.040 --> 09:03.611
Hey, I need you, son.

09:05.750 --> 09:08.127
- You need me?
- Please.

09:13.300 --> 09:14.415
I'll be right there.

09:25.190 --> 09:27.055
Hold still.

09:27.850 --> 09:29.932
I haven't done this in a while.

09:31.610 --> 09:33.066
Maybe I should go
to the hospital.

09:33.780 --> 09:36.772
- I can tell 'em I got mugged.
- The hospital's not safe.

09:37.610 --> 09:39.111
And I can handle a few stitches.

09:39.320 --> 09:40.776
Oops.

09:40.950 --> 09:42.326
What?

09:42.830 --> 09:43.819
Hey.

09:44.200 --> 09:46.111
That's not something
I want to hear right now.

09:46.540 --> 09:47.666
I'm almost done.

09:56.090 --> 09:58.001
I don't think your
ribs are broken, but...

09:59.180 --> 10:01.421
they're pretty badly bruised.

10:02.310 --> 10:04.175
My whole body feels like a bruise.

10:04.810 --> 10:07.768
Well, any tournament of death
you can walk away from...

10:08.060 --> 10:09.186
I still lost.

10:10.610 --> 10:12.726
Sounds like it might have been
rigged to begin with.

10:14.400 --> 10:15.731
Madame Gao...

10:16.950 --> 10:19.987
she gave me a choice to win,
but I couldn't let Sabina die.

10:22.870 --> 10:24.076
Madame Gao.

10:24.870 --> 10:27.998
Not "Mrs Gao" or "Linda Gao."

10:28.870 --> 10:29.871
Why "Madame"?

10:30.790 --> 10:33.418
What, does she run the best little
whorehouse in the Hand or something?

10:35.510 --> 10:37.501
I'll be sure to ask
her once I find her.

10:40.970 --> 10:42.926
After I find out how
she knew my father.

10:43.260 --> 10:44.807
What if Gao was lying?

10:46.020 --> 10:48.591
Just trying to get in your head,
undermine your will to fight her.

10:48.770 --> 10:50.977
It's strategy straight out of
The Art of War.

10:56.740 --> 10:58.389
Oh, it's Claire.

10:58.950 --> 11:00.520
Sabina's safe.

11:09.710 --> 11:12.782
- Just trying to keep the wound clean.
- Yeah.

11:13.750 --> 11:15.126
Okay.

11:16.050 --> 11:17.950
Okay.

11:22.930 --> 11:24.136
Thanks.

11:38.320 --> 11:39.605
What are these for?

11:40.570 --> 11:41.730
'Cause I need a drink.

11:41.990 --> 11:45.482
And you're going to join me,
because I hate drinking alone.

11:55.710 --> 11:56.870
Glass.

12:06.100 --> 12:08.671
Back in the monastery,
Brother Kuo would...

12:09.060 --> 12:12.302
harvest plums every summer
to make wine.

12:12.890 --> 12:15.267
He used to hide it
in these big clay pots,

12:15.810 --> 12:18.563
have it ferment in the bell tower
over the winter.

12:19.740 --> 12:22.140
Me and my friend Davos,
when we were kids, we'd...

12:22.700 --> 12:24.907
we'd wait until the brothers
had gone to sleep

12:25.530 --> 12:27.270
and we'd climb up the tower.

12:29.830 --> 12:33.209
We'd, uh... we'd sneak drinks
and refill the pots with water

12:33.290 --> 12:34.496
so no one knew it was missing.

12:38.960 --> 12:40.291
The wine was so sweet.

12:40.710 --> 12:42.962
In the dead of winter,
it tasted warm...

12:46.340 --> 12:47.341
like summer.

12:48.970 --> 12:49.959
Tell me another one.

12:51.640 --> 12:52.720
Another story.

12:54.140 --> 12:55.186
About K'un-Lun.

12:58.020 --> 13:00.352
Man...

13:03.110 --> 13:04.646
I was there a long time.

13:05.860 --> 13:07.191
They aren't all great memories.

13:11.080 --> 13:12.786
How about how you
got that tattoo?

13:15.080 --> 13:17.287
Well...

13:17.710 --> 13:20.588
...it's not exactly a tattoo.

13:23.470 --> 13:25.119
It's the mark of the Iron Fist.

13:29.600 --> 13:30.715
Danny...

13:31.390 --> 13:35.383
I still do not understand
what that even means.

13:37.980 --> 13:39.106
It's a...

13:41.730 --> 13:43.186
It's a unique force...

13:44.780 --> 13:46.941
used to protect K'un-Lun.

13:47.950 --> 13:51.442
It's passed down from
generation to generation

13:51.950 --> 13:55.283
and it's given to one student
from the monastery to wield.

13:56.370 --> 13:57.917
Why were you chosen to get it?

13:58.330 --> 13:59.706
I wasn't chosen.

14:02.880 --> 14:03.869
I earned it.

14:05.970 --> 14:07.085
Okay, so...

14:09.090 --> 14:10.216
what does it do?

14:10.680 --> 14:12.921
It's complicated.

14:13.270 --> 14:14.305
But it...

14:16.940 --> 14:19.181
lets me harness my chi.

14:20.060 --> 14:21.766
It enhances my strength...

14:22.900 --> 14:23.889
my focus.

14:24.110 --> 14:25.099
And it, um...

14:26.150 --> 14:28.482
makes my hand light up.

14:32.450 --> 14:34.941
Look,
I know it sounds weird, okay?

14:35.160 --> 14:37.287
- I get it.
- Can you show me?

14:37.460 --> 14:40.076
No, I don't think so.

14:41.330 --> 14:43.742
Mm. What, do you think
I can't handle it?

14:44.800 --> 14:46.199
That I'm too weak?

14:46.970 --> 14:50.963
Colleen, you're one of
the strongest people I have ever met.

14:51.140 --> 14:52.880
Anywhere.

14:53.720 --> 14:56.382
I wasn't strong enough
to protect Radovan at the hospital.

14:58.390 --> 14:59.971
Hey,
look, that wasn't your fault.

15:00.690 --> 15:02.351
He was my responsibility.

15:03.820 --> 15:05.310
I was supposed
to protect him...

15:06.860 --> 15:10.159
and now Gao has him again
and we might never be able to find him.

15:14.330 --> 15:15.365
So, yeah...

15:17.450 --> 15:19.077
I guess we both lost tonight.

15:23.040 --> 15:25.747
You're going to keep trying...
aren't you?

15:27.840 --> 15:28.829
To stop...

15:30.260 --> 15:31.716
them?

15:33.600 --> 15:34.885
I can't quit now.

15:38.220 --> 15:39.300
I should go.

15:40.980 --> 15:43.642
- You can stay.
- No, I... I gotta...

15:43.980 --> 15:46.312
go to the office in the morning,
so I should...

15:46.730 --> 15:47.719
Danny...

15:50.280 --> 15:51.486
I want you to stay.

17:30.800 --> 17:32.665
- You sure?
- Yes.

17:35.340 --> 17:37.547
Definitely, yes.

18:40.160 --> 18:42.321
Oh,
Ward, it's about time.

18:53.670 --> 18:55.376
You okay, son?
You look a little green.

18:55.630 --> 18:57.336
Hey, what happened to your hand?

18:57.970 --> 19:00.086
What happened to yours?

19:01.050 --> 19:02.677
Oh, kitchen accident.

19:04.220 --> 19:05.426
Who are they?

19:06.680 --> 19:08.386
Oh, the one without
the tongue is Vando.

19:08.560 --> 19:10.972
The other guy,
I didn't get his name.

19:11.520 --> 19:13.181
The Hand sent them over
to deliver a message.

19:13.360 --> 19:15.521
- We have to call somebody.
- Yeah, I did. I called you.

19:15.860 --> 19:18.272
I need you to take their bodies
to Pelham Bay Park.

19:18.530 --> 19:20.350
Either the cops or the Hand
will find them eventually,

19:20.530 --> 19:23.317
but hopefully we'll be finished
this by then.

19:26.330 --> 19:29.208
They'll find it difficult to identify 'em
without their teeth.

19:31.330 --> 19:33.412
I'm almost ready to
wrap these guys up.

19:33.590 --> 19:36.241
- Then you can put 'em in your car.
- You said you needed me.

19:37.090 --> 19:38.079
Yeah, I do.

19:38.300 --> 19:41.178
You called me in the middle of the night
to dump bodies for you.

19:41.510 --> 19:43.637
Well, who else was
I gonna call, Ward?

19:44.510 --> 19:46.341
I knew you'd come. You always do.

19:52.810 --> 19:54.357
I could do with
an extra hand on this.

19:56.520 --> 19:57.521
Come on.

19:57.730 --> 20:00.392
Just like when we went deer hunting
when you were a kid.

20:00.650 --> 20:02.151
You have to clean your kill.

20:02.780 --> 20:04.316
We never went hunting.

20:04.490 --> 20:05.479
Oh.

20:06.580 --> 20:08.616
Oh, maybe it was your sister.

20:10.370 --> 20:12.531
Well, guess I'll do it myself, then.

20:27.470 --> 20:29.097
Come on!

20:29.890 --> 20:31.050
God.

20:33.020 --> 20:35.056
You can do this.

20:37.980 --> 20:39.220
You can do this.

21:59.940 --> 22:01.146
You think I don't know that?

22:03.740 --> 22:05.890
You think I don't know
how messed up this is?

22:11.660 --> 22:12.820
I'm not a child.

23:31.450 --> 23:32.439
Danny?

23:33.950 --> 23:34.939
Right here.

23:36.830 --> 23:38.240
How long have you been up?

23:38.700 --> 23:39.701
Not long.

23:41.620 --> 23:43.531
The city is always
so quiet this early.

23:54.510 --> 23:55.499
Yeah.

23:56.970 --> 23:57.959
It's nice.

24:01.060 --> 24:02.095
Yeah.

24:07.320 --> 24:08.435
About last night...

24:10.650 --> 24:11.696
Yeah.

24:13.320 --> 24:15.982
I've been living a very different life
for many years.

24:17.160 --> 24:18.650
There are certain
things I haven't...

24:22.620 --> 24:23.666
But last night was...

24:25.710 --> 24:27.792
I enjoyed it.

24:28.920 --> 24:30.410
A lot.

24:36.600 --> 24:37.840
I liked it, too.

24:41.100 --> 24:44.092
You know, this cloak of...

24:44.810 --> 24:48.189
I don't know,
bravado that you have...

24:49.900 --> 24:51.106
I know why you wear it.

24:52.900 --> 24:54.697
I do the same thing.

24:55.110 --> 24:57.237
It keeps people at bay, but...

24:58.740 --> 25:00.696
you know that you don't
have to wear it with me.

25:13.880 --> 25:16.678
Hey, I need you to find
all of my dad's old files.

25:17.090 --> 25:19.217
Okay. They're probably in storage.
Which ones do you want?

25:19.390 --> 25:22.223
Um... Anything
that mentions a woman named Gao.

25:22.390 --> 25:24.051
- Who's that?
- Um...

25:24.390 --> 25:26.642
Just... Just get everything
of my father's. All of it.

25:27.100 --> 25:28.761
And get them to
move it into my office.

25:29.070 --> 25:30.264
It's probably gonna
be a lot of files.

25:30.400 --> 25:32.311
Well, I have a pretty big office.

25:33.190 --> 25:35.442
- Danny.
- Oh, Joy, I was just about to...

25:35.610 --> 25:36.736
We need to talk.

25:37.700 --> 25:38.689
Now.

25:40.330 --> 25:41.319
Okay.

25:42.160 --> 25:43.286
"My actions were impulsive,

25:43.500 --> 25:45.741
and I_ now realise
the severity of my words."

25:47.170 --> 25:48.159
Is this an apology?

25:48.500 --> 25:51.549
No, it's the statement
you're gonna be making

25:51.710 --> 25:53.007
at the board meeting this afternoon.

25:54.510 --> 25:55.966
It sort of seems like an apology.

25:56.300 --> 25:57.289
Well...

25:58.050 --> 25:59.756
apologies are what got you
into this disaster,

25:59.930 --> 26:02.842
so, yeah,
officially, it's a statement.

26:03.720 --> 26:07.019
It's the first step of CIR's plan
to save the company's image.

26:08.150 --> 26:10.391
But... But what about the plant?

26:10.570 --> 26:11.559
What about it?

26:12.650 --> 26:16.063
- It might be making people sick.
- Danny, we don't know what's causing it.

26:16.400 --> 26:17.856
The EPA cleared us.

26:18.450 --> 26:20.270
Fifteen cases_of_cancer
can't be a comcrdence.

26:23.370 --> 26:26.248
Do you think that I don't care
about those people?

26:27.210 --> 26:28.199
I do.

26:28.620 --> 26:30.417
But I also care
about this company.

26:30.630 --> 26:33.702
And right now, I seem to be the only one
here who is taking this seriously.

26:33.880 --> 26:35.336
I mean, I have no idea where Ward is.

26:36.300 --> 26:38.427
And you don't even show up
for the CIR meeting.

26:38.720 --> 26:41.462
And when you do show up to work,
your face is beat to shit?

26:42.850 --> 26:44.670
You're the one that wanted
Into this company, rIght?

26:45.180 --> 26:46.590
You fought like hell to get it.

26:47.100 --> 26:50.809
Well, now is the time
for the hard work to actually start.

26:51.650 --> 26:56.064
I need you to just do what I say
at this meeting today

26:56.240 --> 26:58.526
so we can get
this situation fixed.

27:01.950 --> 27:04.077
- Danny?
- Hey, I'll be there, okay?

27:09.210 --> 27:12.282
You really need to take
better care of yourself, Danny.

27:13.460 --> 27:16.543
This room has
terrible feng shui.

27:17.720 --> 27:19.119
Too many angles.

27:20.010 --> 27:23.298
Poison arrows _
can weaken the soul over tIme.

27:25.970 --> 27:27.426
That's better.
Don't you agree?

27:27.980 --> 27:29.345
How did you get in here?

27:30.600 --> 27:33.558
I've been in Rand
far longer than you have.

27:34.150 --> 27:36.857
And I don't plan
on leaving anytime soon.

27:39.860 --> 27:45.071
You're not going to attack an old woman
in front of all your employees, are you?

27:45.490 --> 27:49.529
I think Danny Rand is in
enough trouble around here.

27:50.250 --> 27:51.365
I passed your test.

27:53.000 --> 27:53.989
You know who I am.

27:54.500 --> 27:55.626
What I can do.

27:57.130 --> 28:01.920
You're not the first I've met _
to carry the mantle of the Iron FIst.

28:03.050 --> 28:05.462
Is that why you use that symbol
on your heroin packages?

28:06.180 --> 28:08.057
The dragon without the wings?

28:08.890 --> 28:12.223
The other Iron Fists I've known
were fierce,

28:12.770 --> 28:17.013
unrelenting in their mission
to protect K'un-Lun from the Hand.

28:18.190 --> 28:21.318
They would never have backed down
from a grand duel

28:21.490 --> 28:24.152
just to save the life of one girl.

28:27.490 --> 28:28.536
How did you know my father?

28:31.960 --> 28:38.331
I've been alive long enough
to watch the world change in many ways.

28:39.380 --> 28:43.828
But this change now,
it feels significant.

28:45.050 --> 28:47.553
The Devil of Hell's Kitchen.

28:47.850 --> 28:50.387
The man with unbreakable skin.

28:50.850 --> 28:54.968
And now, an immortal weapon
has left K'un-Lun,

28:55.230 --> 28:59.769
not to fulfil his duty,
but in dereliction of it.

